    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>In your code, you are not merging. To fix, the code will be like this</p>\n\n<pre><code>    PDFMergerUtility mergerUtility = new PDFMergerUtility();\n    try  {\n        while(rs.next())    {      \n            in=resultset.getBinaryStream(1);\n            mergerUtility.addSource(in);\n\n        }       \n        mergerUtility.setDestinationStream(bos);\n        mergerUtility.mergeDocuments();\n\n        bos.close();\n\n   }\n   catch (Exception e) { \n\n   }\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1681237,
      "reputation" : 1889,
      "user_id" : 1545425,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/GmowT.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Luca Tampellini",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1545425/luca-tampellini"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1764174057,
    "creation_date" : 1764174057,
    "answer_id" : 79830927,
    "question_id" : 13818706,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>posting here as I have been stumbling in the same issue : <em>the root of your problem, as it was in my case, is that <strong>one cannot re-use the same instance of a PDFMergerUtility for 2 or more separate merges</strong>, 1 new instance per every emerge</em>!</p>\n<p>At least, it is currently so for versions of Pdfbox up to vrs. 3.0.6</p>\n"
  } ],
